snippet.textDisplay:
thought this was about her struggle with reaching insane levels of fame?? yet I haven't seen anyone suggest it here?
I'll just throw in my 2cents for the interpretation
"I had a dream I got everything I wanted... And if I'm being honest I think it was a nightmare" at first wanting fame, achieving it, then realising it didn't make her as happy as she hoped
"Thought I could fly, so I stepped off the golden" thought she could handle the pressures of fame
"Nobody cried, nobody even noticed, I saw them standing right there, kinda thought they might care" as she began to rise to fame and began suffering from the pressure no one around her noticed or paid attention to it, likely only caring about her continuous rise upwards to fame
"But when I wake up I see you with me, and you say as long as I'm here no one can hurt you" In the chaos of her rapid rise to fame and possible struggle with it her brother has been the one by her side actually caring about her. This is probably why she's brought him more into the spotlight next to her recently, for support as well to give him recognition she thinks he deserves.
"don't want to lie here, but you can learn to, if I could change the way the way that you see yourself, you wouldn't wonder why you're here..." Since they wrote this together it may be both sides, not feeling comfortable in the spotlight so much or wanting to be there and feeling undeserving, and the other reassuring them they are deserving
"If I knew it all then, would I do it again?" If she had the chance to go back to the beginning would she take the fame route again or choose a different one

To be honest I don't really know much about Billie or her music, but this song interested me! I don't mean any harm from this and I could totally be wrong! In fact I hope I am

snippet.textDisplay: My head went to fucked up places as a teen and on top of it I have clinical depression. Shes a very happy go lucky girl, but suffers from mental health battles while being a teen and she expresses it through songs. Only a certain audience will get where this pain comes from. Some of you are judging amd dont have depression OR you do , but not as severe as hers. You have to be able to relate to a persons music so if you dont like it, it was not ment to be unserstood by people like you. Im 25 with 2 boys and this in a way is weird for me, but i look back on my teenager years, foster care, abuse etc and man did my mind go into a place of darkness and followed me everywhere even with medication. I used to write my stuff in a journal. Billie is singing the diary if her pain. Try to understand if you can.

snippet.textDisplay: If you are thinking about ending your life, please talk to someone about it. That level of depression and pain takes away your ability to see your life with any degree of perspective. It skews the way you think and feel, and even changes the kind of thoughts you have in the darkest way. It also distorts the way you experience time- even though you haven't felt the way you feel now forever, it feels like it is forever. Don't believe this -GET HELP. Please know, if you tear yourself out of the fabric of life, the people you leave behind will be suffering for the rest of their lives. You're a human being in pain and you deserve to receive care and help. Depression is a disorder of brain function that can be treated. Let people help you. Human love isn't perfect, but it's real. Let people love you. With treatment you'll find it's possible to fall in love with life again.
